  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c 10\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd8\u0dad \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dba \u0dba\u0da7\u0dad\u0dda \u0d86\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Permission to import 10 essential food items under open account system",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet approves re-importation of rice, flour, white sugar, red dhal, milk powder, big onions, potatoes, dried chillies, dried sprats and Watana lentils in limited quantities under the open account scheme from July 1. Has been decided. That is for a period of two months from the 1st of July.",
        "The decision was taken by the Cabinet on the idea of \u200b\u200bMinister of Commerce and Food Security Nalin Fernando to provide essential food items to the consumers without any shortage."
      ],
